WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:05.846
NARRATOR: For centuries,
mankind has been the dominant species.

00:06.173 --> 00:11.145
We've domesticated animals,
locked them up, killed them for sport.

00:11.303 --> 00:13.647
But a series of recent
events seem to suggest

00:13.805 --> 00:18.436
all across the globe animals
have decided "no more."

00:18.810 --> 00:20.232
And so we were hired,

00:20.395 --> 00:22.489
a team of people from
different backgrounds,

00:22.648 --> 00:24.241
with different specialties.

00:24.399 --> 00:26.401
An expert in animal behavior,

00:26.568 --> 00:28.036
a journalist,

00:28.195 --> 00:29.697
safari guide,

00:29.863 --> 00:31.490
foreign intelligence agent,

00:31.657 --> 00:34.251
and a veterinary pathologist.

00:34.409 --> 00:37.037
Our task: to Hnd out what is
happening with the animals,

00:37.579 --> 00:41.209
why it's happening,
and how to stop it.

00:43.126 --> 00:44.548
Previously on Zoo.'

00:44.711 --> 00:47.464
The global pandemic your father
believes was about to emerge,

00:47.631 --> 00:49.508
it appears it has arrived.

00:49.675 --> 00:53.225
And that's why I had Monsieur Alves
bring the five of you together.

00:53.387 --> 00:55.810
If you're not happy with the
way I'm handling my assignment,

00:55.973 --> 00:57.395
you can feel free to replace me.

00:57.558 --> 01:00.357
But until then, I'm gonna try
to do my best to reverse it.

01:00.519 --> 01:03.147
And the answer to the question
you haven't asked me yet is no,

01:03.313 --> 01:05.072
I'm not gonna cut loose
the member of my team

01:05.232 --> 01:06.654
who killed Agent Ben Shafer.

01:06.817 --> 01:10.037
MAN: All evidence suggests she's
the one who shot Ben. Go get her.

01:10.988 --> 01:15.038
I think these lions are communicating
with each other. Long distance.

01:15.659 --> 01:19.709
The Mother Cell is in every
single product Reiden makes.

01:20.205 --> 01:23.334
It's everywhere.
It's all over the world.

01:23.500 --> 01:24.626
And it can't be stopped.

01:26.044 --> 01:27.842
JAMIE: We got it.
This could be the answer.

01:28.005 --> 01:30.053
The Mother Cell can
cure the animals?

01:30.215 --> 01:32.217
Dr. Morgan believes so, yes.

01:32.384 --> 01:34.307
And he says that he
has the Mother Cell

01:34.469 --> 01:37.188
and he's willing to give it back,
but he needs something in return.

01:37.347 --> 01:39.566
I have to tell my
daughter why she's dying.

01:39.725 --> 01:41.398
Your drug will cure her.

01:41.560 --> 01:43.938
Her name's Clementine. She's 10.

01:44.104 --> 01:46.232
I'll expect a call from
you within 48 hours

01:46.398 --> 01:48.617
telling me where and when
I can get my medicine.

01:54.906 --> 01:57.910
CLAYTON: There should be more than
enough here to help your daughter.

01:58.076 --> 02:00.124
It's a six-week
course of treatment.

02:00.287 --> 02:04.713
The protocol is simple,
two pills, three times a day.

02:31.860 --> 02:34.283
The Mother Cell, please.

02:36.865 --> 02:38.913
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

02:42.120 --> 02:43.713
[BUzzlNG]

02:44.665 --> 02:45.962
Now, please.

02:46.124 --> 02:48.547
And I'll still let
you keep the medicine.

03:17.489 --> 03:19.491
This is Delavane.
Alert security.

03:19.658 --> 03:22.161
We have an intruder on
the executive floor.

03:22.327 --> 03:27.128
White male, approximately 6 feet
tall, brown hair, glasses.

03:27.582 --> 03:28.879
[ELEVATOR DINGs]

03:50.272 --> 03:52.320
- Where is he?
- Don't know.

03:52.482 --> 03:54.325
Elevator 3 has been
stopping on every floor

03:54.484 --> 03:56.361
and the camera inside
is blacked out.

03:56.528 --> 03:58.030
Start a floor-to-floor search.

03:58.196 --> 04:00.290
He does not leave this
building, you understand me?

04:00.449 --> 04:02.167
Yes, sir.

04:02.617 --> 04:05.211
All security personnel,
activate lockdown...

04:05.370 --> 04:07.793
Now, you don't need to tell me.

04:07.956 --> 04:09.674
He's one of your team.

04:09.833 --> 04:11.585
Mitch Morgan.

04:11.752 --> 04:13.754
What in God's name
was he doing here?

04:21.720 --> 04:23.563
Of course.

04:24.556 --> 04:26.558
[ALARM WAILING]

04:50.582 --> 04:51.629
Damn it.

05:37.212 --> 05:38.839
Are you still standing there?

05:39.005 --> 05:40.507
MAN: Yes, sir.

05:40.674 --> 05:42.142
Why?

05:42.300 --> 05:44.473
MAN: It's about Agent Shafer.

05:46.763 --> 05:48.390
What about him?

05:48.557 --> 05:50.980
Agent Shafer was in
Biloxi on his own time.

05:51.142 --> 05:53.190
No official case
logs, no files, nada.

05:53.895 --> 05:55.192
I know that, Agent Singer.

05:56.648 --> 05:58.400
Well, I was going through
his phone records,

05:58.567 --> 06:00.990
and he received multiple
calls from a Chloe Tousignant.

06:03.238 --> 06:04.865
Tousignant.

06:05.031 --> 06:07.204
Wait a minute, I know that name.

06:10.704 --> 06:12.297
Passenger manifests.

06:13.123 --> 06:14.750
Here.

06:15.876 --> 06:18.504
I remember thinking,
"How do you pronounce that name?"

06:18.670 --> 06:21.719
As it turns out,
she's on leave from the DGSE.

06:21.882 --> 06:23.134
She's in French intelligence?

06:25.051 --> 06:26.598
Oxymoron.

06:27.178 --> 06:30.603
"28A. Chloe Tousignant."

06:30.765 --> 06:34.861
She and Jamie Campbell are on the
same flight from Tokyo to Biloxi.

06:36.897 --> 06:39.696
She's in D.C.
at the same time as Campbell.

06:39.858 --> 06:40.905
Good work, agent.

06:41.067 --> 06:43.161
Dig deep on Tousignant.
I wanna know who she is

06:43.320 --> 06:46.369
and who she was talking to before
and after she arrived in Mobile.

06:46.740 --> 06:48.492
You got it, sir.

06:52.996 --> 06:54.998
Oh, my God, you bastard.

06:55.165 --> 06:58.044
- It was for my daughter.
- Even so.

06:58.209 --> 07:01.759
If you could've saved your mother,
you wouldn't have done the same?

07:03.089 --> 07:04.136
CHLOE: So you did it?

07:04.507 --> 07:06.930
You traded the Mother
Cell for the medicine.

07:10.388 --> 07:12.436
No. I didn't.

07:14.267 --> 07:15.484
But you almost did.

07:15.644 --> 07:16.987
Yeah, I almost did.

07:17.812 --> 07:20.031
- For my daughter.
- We're here trying to do this,

07:20.190 --> 07:22.238
trying to come up with a
solution for everything,

07:22.400 --> 07:24.152
and you would just
give that away?

07:24.319 --> 07:25.866
Look.

07:26.029 --> 07:29.499
While I'm not trying
to minimize any of it,

07:29.950 --> 07:32.874
you're all focusing on the
wrong guy right now. Okay?

07:33.036 --> 07:35.380
Delavane?
Not who we think he is.

07:35.538 --> 07:37.040
How can you be so sure?

07:37.207 --> 07:38.834
Maybe he had a good
reason to be there.

07:39.250 --> 07:41.002
Get serious.

07:41.169 --> 07:43.046
I saw his face. Trust me.

07:43.213 --> 07:44.840
You're asking us to trust you?

07:45.006 --> 07:49.056
I'm asking you to call my character
into question at a later date.

07:49.678 --> 07:50.895
Delavane was not at Reiden

07:51.054 --> 07:54.934
because it was Bring Your Shadowy
Interpol Agent to the Office Day.

07:55.100 --> 07:56.818
He was there because
he works there.

07:57.852 --> 07:58.944
Did he see you?

08:04.901 --> 08:07.905
- This is bad.
- So you're saying...

08:08.279 --> 08:10.782
The company that put us
together is the same company

08:10.949 --> 08:12.201
that we're trying to take down?

08:13.410 --> 08:15.913
- It appears that way.
- But why?

08:16.079 --> 08:17.547
Why would Delavane
put us together

08:17.706 --> 08:20.004
if there was even a chance
of us uncovering the truth?

08:20.166 --> 08:21.839
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

08:23.670 --> 08:24.922
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

08:25.088 --> 08:27.716
PASCAL [IN FRENCH]:

08:37.808 --> 08:39.311
[IN ENGLISH] So,
what else, Mitch?

08:39.477 --> 08:43.152
- What else what?
- What else are you lying to us about?

08:43.313 --> 08:48.195
Okay. The Mother Cell,
can we really use it to make a cure?

08:48.361 --> 08:52.992
Yes. Theoretically,
it can be used to reverse the mutation.

08:53.158 --> 08:54.330
Theoretically?

08:54.492 --> 08:56.620
I believe that if we
introduce the Mother Cell

08:56.786 --> 08:59.039
into the DNA of
a mutated animal,

08:59.205 --> 09:01.458
we could possibly
synthesize a cure.

09:01.624 --> 09:03.126
But here's the problem.

09:03.626 --> 09:07.176
In order to do that,
we need an animal who has mutated

09:07.338 --> 09:09.932
and has not been exposed
to the Mother Cell.

09:10.091 --> 09:11.843
But does such an
animal even exist?

09:12.010 --> 09:14.263
Every animal we've
come into Contact with

09:14.429 --> 09:15.897
has been mutated
because of Reiden.

09:16.056 --> 09:18.900
Even if there is,
how would we possibly find it?

09:19.059 --> 09:22.029
There are infected animals
on every continent.

09:22.187 --> 09:25.441
I know. It's like trying to find
a needle in a stack of needles.

09:25.607 --> 09:27.826
In every country on Earth.

09:27.984 --> 09:30.828
But without that needle,
we don't have a cure.

09:33.239 --> 09:35.207
PASCAL [IN FRENCH]:

09:38.495 --> 09:40.964
CHLOE:

09:49.172 --> 09:51.095
- [IN ENGLISH] We have to go.
- What happened?

09:51.257 --> 09:53.726
That was my colleague
at the DGSE.

09:53.885 --> 09:57.515
The FBI has issued a warrant for my arrest.
Jamie's too.

09:58.056 --> 10:02.277
Ben Shafer. Oh, my God, Chloe.
I'm so sorry.

10:02.435 --> 10:04.813
There's nothing
to apologize for.

10:04.979 --> 10:07.459
It's only a matter of time before
they connect the rest of you.

10:09.234 --> 10:10.360
We have to go, guys.

10:10.527 --> 10:13.371
Hey, hey, hold on.
Go where? Huh?

10:13.530 --> 10:14.827
If the FBI is after us,

10:14.989 --> 10:16.912
if Delavane works for
Reiden, where we gonna go?

10:17.075 --> 10:19.919
Yeah, I don't speak spy...

10:20.703 --> 10:22.421
But it pretty much
feels like game over.

10:29.129 --> 10:30.551
[Dos BARKING]

10:30.713 --> 10:32.681
Henry's a lucky dog.
He's in perfect health.

10:32.841 --> 10:34.343
- So no more pills?
- No more pills.

10:34.509 --> 10:35.949
Do you think he's
ever gonna be able

10:36.094 --> 10:37.846
to help Clementine with
her seizures again?

10:38.012 --> 10:40.435
I'm hopeful.
It may just take some more time.

10:41.141 --> 10:42.939
We'll see you in a couple of
months, Henry.

10:43.434 --> 10:47.234
You just take care of this
nice family of yours, okay?

10:47.772 --> 10:50.116
MAN: Tell me what's going on.
- I don't know what happened.

10:50.275 --> 10:52.994
They just started
making that awful noise.

10:53.153 --> 10:54.200
It's okay. Shh.

11:04.789 --> 11:07.292
Come on, Henry.

11:09.586 --> 11:11.213
Good boy.

11:13.506 --> 11:15.508
[CONTINUES BARKING]

11:15.675 --> 11:17.848
[BIRDs sQuA\/\/KING]

11:24.225 --> 11:25.477
Come on, let's go inside.

11:28.730 --> 11:31.984
Maybe we should not be standing
around in a clump like this.

11:33.026 --> 11:35.626
Like the lady said, "if they're
going to treat us like criminals",

11:35.737 --> 11:37.284
we need to act like criminals."

11:37.447 --> 11:39.575
Everybody gets one.

11:40.158 --> 11:41.838
CHLOE: Any calls you
make, keep them short.

11:41.993 --> 11:44.246
From now on,
we pay cash for everything.

11:44.412 --> 11:46.790
And no more Contact
with family and friends.

11:46.956 --> 11:48.156
Yeah, that's not gonna happen.

11:48.291 --> 11:49.543
- Not for me, anyway.
- Why not?

11:49.709 --> 11:51.803
Because I gotta get
these meds to Clem.

11:51.961 --> 11:54.555
And FBI or not,
I'm bringing them to her.

11:54.714 --> 11:56.842
[slREN vvAll_lNG]

12:02.472 --> 12:04.770
All right, guys, stop.
Just stop.

12:04.933 --> 12:06.435
This, this isn't gonna work.

12:06.601 --> 12:09.525
We can't just be reactive to this thing.
We gotta get out in front of it.

12:09.687 --> 12:13.032
We've been together a couple months
as a team, doing pretty good, so now.

12:13.191 --> 12:15.694
Now we gotta save our own asses
and we gotta save the world.

12:16.319 --> 12:20.199
- That's a bit dramatic, but well said.
CHLOE: Agreed.

12:20.365 --> 12:21.491
What's the plan?

12:21.658 --> 12:25.208
All right, tirst off,
it's time to go public with this thing.

12:25.745 --> 12:28.464
Now, we need a more official
outlet than your blog, Jamie,

12:28.623 --> 12:31.023
but we obviously can't risk just
walking into a news station.

12:31.167 --> 12:33.261
Who do you know?
Do you know someone you can contact?

12:33.753 --> 12:35.881
- Yeah.
- Okay. Abe,

12:36.047 --> 12:39.301
take Mitch and the car and go
get those meds to Clementine.

12:40.843 --> 12:42.220
Okay.

12:42.387 --> 12:43.434
What about us?

12:43.596 --> 12:45.724
I've got an idea for us.

12:49.602 --> 12:52.606
Why wasn't I told about the
existence of this Mother Cell?

12:52.772 --> 12:54.115
You're head of global security.

12:54.274 --> 12:57.278
There are many things that you
need to know about to do your job.

12:57.443 --> 12:58.740
Mother Cell wasn't one of them.

12:58.903 --> 13:00.826
I made it very clear when
I took this project on

13:00.989 --> 13:02.161
I needed to know everything.

13:02.323 --> 13:04.200
Information is a two-way street.

13:04.367 --> 13:05.914
Imagine my surprise
when I learned

13:06.077 --> 13:08.546
that I was being blackmailed
by a member of your team.

13:08.705 --> 13:11.049
I couldn't possibly have known
about Mitch Morgan's plan.

13:11.207 --> 13:12.959
No, but you knew they
found the Mother Cell.

13:13.126 --> 13:15.504
Yes, and had I known of its
significance to the company,

13:15.670 --> 13:17.798
I would have dealt
with it appropriately.

13:17.964 --> 13:20.467
Look, we can go around in
circles like this forever.

13:20.633 --> 13:23.386
The point is, you kept me in the
dark and compromised the operation.

13:23.553 --> 13:27.274
The point is that this team
of yours was put together

13:27.432 --> 13:29.230
to protect this
company's position,

13:29.392 --> 13:32.271
and they now possess the very
device that can destroy us.

13:32.437 --> 13:35.941
Find them, get the Mother
Cell back and end this.

14:07.305 --> 14:08.352
Sasha.

14:08.514 --> 14:11.233
Ah. Good, you're home. Mwah.

14:11.392 --> 14:14.145
- I was running out of small talk.
- Hm?

14:14.312 --> 14:16.406
- Your friends are here.
- What?

14:20.485 --> 14:22.988
You never mentioned Tommy
was in the Air Force.

14:23.571 --> 14:26.575
After talking with Sasha,
we feel like we barely know you.

14:28.117 --> 14:29.915
Excuse me.

14:35.208 --> 14:37.552
MAN: This is Wilson.
- Wilson, it's .Jamie Campbell.

14:37.710 --> 14:40.589
- Jamie, how are you?
- I have a story for you. I'm in Boston.

14:40.755 --> 14:43.929
A story for me. Why do you have a
story for me and not a story for you?

14:44.092 --> 14:45.139
It's complicated.

14:45.301 --> 14:47.144
- Can we meet?
- Sure, just come by the ofHce.

14:47.303 --> 14:49.772
I can't do that.
Like I said, it's complicated.

14:49.931 --> 14:52.605
Is there anywhere that we
can make this discreet?

14:52.767 --> 14:53.984
What's going on, Jamie?

14:54.143 --> 14:58.364
Look, this is... This is big, Wilson.
Career-defining.

14:58.523 --> 15:02.153
I have to be an anonymous source
at the outset, but not for long.

15:02.318 --> 15:03.991
I just need someone I can trust.

15:05.196 --> 15:06.789
You're serious.

15:07.365 --> 15:08.412
Okay.

15:08.825 --> 15:12.830
Two o'clock. There's a warehouse at
the corner of Madison and 3rd Street.

15:13.496 --> 15:14.543
Are you in trouble, Jamie?

15:16.290 --> 15:19.760
I'm okay. Thanks, Wilson. Uh...

15:19.919 --> 15:22.138
Two o'clock, I'll see you then.

15:30.930 --> 15:32.490
MITCH: Yeah,
I'll meet you at the house.

15:32.974 --> 15:35.272
Anything comes up,
just call me on this number.

15:35.810 --> 15:37.938
Yeah, I had to change phones.

15:38.104 --> 15:39.697
It's a long story.

15:39.856 --> 15:42.700
Okay. Bye.

15:44.026 --> 15:46.279
We're going to your ex's house?

15:46.446 --> 15:49.791
Maybe we should go somewhere that
the police wouldn't think of,

15:49.949 --> 15:51.451
just in case.

15:51.617 --> 15:54.336
Yeah, it might be the
worst idea I've ever had.

15:54.495 --> 15:57.123
But thank you for
coming with me.

15:57.999 --> 16:02.095
I'm not doing this for you.
I'm doing this for your daughter.

16:03.796 --> 16:06.299
Look,
I know what I did was wrong.

16:07.091 --> 16:08.513
If it's gonna make
you feel better,

16:09.093 --> 16:11.061
take a swing at me.

16:11.762 --> 16:13.890
Serious, go ahead.

16:20.563 --> 16:24.739
Believe me, that's the last
thing you want right now. Heh.

16:30.573 --> 16:31.950
[sQUAwKING]

16:32.950 --> 16:35.123
That sound is not normal, is it?

16:35.620 --> 16:38.624
I'd say that's pretty
far from normal.

16:39.957 --> 16:41.425
Tah!

16:45.880 --> 16:48.724
Couple of months
ago in Cape Town,

16:48.883 --> 16:50.403
the crew of a fishing
trawler reported

16:50.551 --> 16:53.304
how a flock of razorbills
attacked their boat.

16:53.763 --> 16:56.482
People were convinced they
were after their haul of squid.

16:56.641 --> 17:00.691
But the captain was convinced
they were after the crew.

17:01.229 --> 17:03.152
He described the sound
the razorbills made

17:03.314 --> 17:05.863
as they circled
overhead, like cicadas.

17:08.486 --> 17:09.578
Let's get out of here.

17:09.737 --> 17:12.080
Yes. You drive.

17:13.950 --> 17:15.998
Beautiful home.

17:16.618 --> 17:19.247
My guess is that a government agent
couldn't afford the water bill

17:19.413 --> 17:21.540
for a place like this.

17:22.250 --> 17:24.173
Good thing you're not
a government agent.

17:24.335 --> 17:26.929
You have no idea who I am.

17:27.088 --> 17:28.806
Or what I am capable of.

17:28.965 --> 17:32.265
You work for Reiden Global.
That is all we need to know.

17:32.426 --> 17:34.053
Maybe.

17:34.220 --> 17:36.018
Maybe not.

17:37.765 --> 17:40.393
On the other hand,
I put your team together.

17:40.560 --> 17:43.655
- I know everything about you.
- Exactly.

17:43.813 --> 17:45.030
Why would you do that?

17:45.189 --> 17:47.157
Especially if you knew
Reiden was responsible

17:47.316 --> 17:49.660
for the very thing you
wanted us to investigate.

17:49.819 --> 17:52.572
Our culpability is hardly
a foregone conclusion.

17:52.738 --> 17:54.490
Oh, it will be when we're done.

17:54.657 --> 17:56.625
The I\/Iother Cell's
pretty damning proof.

17:58.286 --> 17:59.788
Why are you here?

17:59.954 --> 18:01.547
What do you want?

18:02.164 --> 18:07.136
We want what you promised
when you hired us.

18:07.295 --> 18:09.548
Resources, information, access.

18:09.714 --> 18:12.012
We want you to
help us make a cure

18:12.174 --> 18:14.597
to reverse the changes we're
seeing in the animal kingdom,

18:14.760 --> 18:18.560
and we want you to come clean.

18:18.723 --> 18:20.771
Let the world know
about the Mother Cell

18:20.933 --> 18:23.311
- and Reiden's role in all of this.
- Heh-heh.

18:23.477 --> 18:25.320
Clearly you're not that naive.

18:25.479 --> 18:29.234
If we do that, we will be met by
billions of dollars of lawsuits,

18:29.400 --> 18:30.822
Reiden will be destroyed.

18:30.985 --> 18:34.410
We are offering you a chance
to be part of the solution.

18:34.572 --> 18:36.995
Do that and maybe, just maybe,

18:37.158 --> 18:39.252
the court of public opinion
will go easy on you.

18:42.413 --> 18:45.633
I have a different suggestion.

18:45.791 --> 18:50.171
You give me the I\/Iother
Cell and I let you walk away.

18:51.297 --> 18:52.719
What's that mean?

18:52.882 --> 18:55.226
I'm very good at my
job, Miss Tousignant.

18:55.384 --> 18:59.059
I know the FBI just issued
a warrant for your arrest

18:59.221 --> 19:00.939
and that of Miss Campbell.

19:01.098 --> 19:03.692
Soon, they will link the rest
of you to Agent Shafer's murder,

